## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of crime in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Crime is the bounded violation structure
through which prohibited acts,
alleged acts,
investigation,
disposition,
and historical offense records
become meaningful.

## canonical_rules
- allegation is not conviction
- investigation is not final disposition
- historical offense trace must remain distinguishable
- ambiguous crime status fails closed
